creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 126 by Various.
Read in English by LaMar Hawkins; Ben Lindsey-Clark; Drew Johnson; Winston Tharp; Rhys Harrison; Kasper Nijsen; Olivereading; Frances Brown; Sue Anderson

This is a collection of 20 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for November 2013. This collection includes the following:
The Deserted House by Alfred, Lord Tennyson
The Dong With A Luminous Nose by Edward Lear
Dulce Et Decorum Est by Wilfred Owen
An Epistle from Corinth by William Alexander Percy
Ghosts by Marguerite Mooers Marshall
Hope by Joseph Addison
Hymn to Proserpine by Algernon Charles Swinburne
Jabberwocky by Lewis Carroll
The Jumblies by Edward Lear
Landing of the Pilgrims by Felicia Dorothea Hemans
Maldive Shark by Herman Melville
Men Improve With the Years by William Butler Yeats
My First Cigar by Robert Jones Burdette
The Birds and the Leaves (November) by Alice Cary
Now is the Accepted Time by Edward Carpenter
The Owl Critic by James Thomas Fields
Plainte Eternelle by Lord Alfred Douglas
The Pumpkin by John Greenleaf Whittier
Reconciliation by Walt Whitman
Sunday Morning by Wallace Stevens

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available

title: Short Poetry Collection 126

reviews.reviewbody: The reading of Deserted House is pure genius. The two seperate voices read by one person; pure genius!
